   <text>
      <body>
         <pb facs="1874_11_07_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Buchheister_Shanghai_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="left">
               <del rend="overstrike">
                  <hi rend="print">J. J.</hi>
               </del>
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01116">
                  <hi rend="print">BUCHHEISTER.</hi>+C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               </orgName>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="print">
                  <placeName ref="K00503">SHANGHAI</placeName>.</hi>
            </seg>
            <seg rend="right">
               <date when="1874-11-07">7 November 1874</date>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="center">Messrs <orgName type="firm" ref="K01004">L. Kniffler +C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               </orgName>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName>
            </seg>
            <lb/> Dear Sirs, Your favor of the <date when="1874-11-04">4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>inst</abbr>
                  <expan>instant</expan>
               </choice>
            </date> is duly received<lb/> + contents thankfully noted.<lb/>
            <hi rend="underline">Cannons.</hi> please buy for us and send by <hi rend="underline">cheap</hi> oppor-<lb/> tunity the<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>2 <term type="goods" ref="K01638">Whitworth smoothbore</term> 6 pars</cell>
                  <cell rows="2">
                     <lb/>of best terms obtainable.</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>+2 ＂ <term type="goods" ref="K01638">rifles</term> 12
                                <unclear>pars</unclear>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table> About the other guns we would feel obliged by
                some<lb/>
                more particulars. We send you three black forms<lb/> which please return after
                having filled in what details<lb/> you can get from the owner, after which we
                will<lb/> see whether we can make an offer. Drawings or better<lb/> still
                photographs would greatly facilitate business.<lb/> Are there any cheap old smooth
                bone <hi rend="underline">iron</hi> guns<lb/> to be had in <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName> or other ports of Japan? If so<lb/> please state weight
                and price per <term type="measure" ref="K01504">picul</term>.<lb/>
            <hi rend="underline">Vessel for <placeName ref="K00528">Hakodadi</placeName> + <term type="goods" ref="K01501">Coals</term>
            </hi>
            <seg rend="right">we still want a vessel<lb/> but are afraid that present <term type="goods" ref="K01501">coal</term>
            </seg>
            <lb/> freights will prevent you from chartering. Please<lb/> not to <del rend="overstrike">lost</del>
            <add style="textOrientation: straight" resp="writer" place="above">lose</add> sight
                of it however.<lb/>
            <seg rend="left">
               <term type="commercial" ref="K01508">Mex $</term>
               <measure type="currency" quantity="74.925" unit="mex$">74.92<hi rend="superscript">5.</hi>
               </measure>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00523">London</placeName> 6 <hi rend="superscript">m</hi>/s Bps
                    5/9 ⅛</seg>
            <seg rend="right">Yoursfaithfully<lb/>
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01116">Buchheister+C<hi rend="underline">o</hi>
               </orgName>
            </seg>
         </p>
